abstract: Israel Electric Corporation will return electric power to Palestinian areas of West Bank after receiving $75 million payment from Israeli government; money will be deducted from Palestinian tax revenues that are currently being withheld.
lead_paragraph: The state-owned electric company, which briefly reduced power on two days this week, has reached a deal with the Israeli government to help offset what it is owed.

headline.main: Israeli Utility to Stop Disrupting Electricity in West Bank
headline.print_headline: Electricity to Return to West Bank
